[src:ellipsoid-method/ellipsoid-method] Consider a family of convex optimization problems of the form: **minimize *f*(*x*) s.t.
[src:ellipsoid-method/ellipsoid-method] *x* is in *G***, where *f* is a convex function and *G* is a convex set (a subset of an Euclidean space *Rn*).
[src:ellipsoid-method/ellipsoid-method] Each problem *p* in the family is represented by a data-vector Data(*p*), e.g., the real-valued coefficients in matrices and vectors representing the function *f* and the feasible region *G*.
[src:ellipsoid-method/ellipsoid-method] The *size* of a problem *p*, Size(*p*), is defined as the number of elements (real numbers) in Data(*p*).
[src:ellipsoid-method/ellipsoid-method] Under these assumptions, the ellipsoid method is "R-polynomial".
